The `isPrime` function checks if the given number is less than 2 (which is not prime) and then loops through each number from 2 up to the square root of the input number, checking if the input number is divisible by any of those numbers. If it is divisible by any number in the loop, it returns false, indicating that the number is not prime. If the loop completes without finding any factors of the input number, it returns true, indicating that the number is prime.

